data.title: Tennessee Zip Code Listings 2020
data.text:
Tennessee Zip Codes 2020

At 42,143 square miles Tennessee is the 36th largest state in America. Administratively Tennessee is divided into 6,711 cities and towns and 95 counties. The state's population in 2013 was 6,495,978 making it the 17th most populous city in America.

As of January 2014, the state has roughly 786 zip codes, which are listed below with the respective city, town, village or location name as well as the area code. The capital is Nashville (2010 population: 626,681) and the largest city is Memphis (2012 population: 655,155).
